However, its effectiveness depends to a large extent on the combination of many components of the formula, whose composition differs according to the diagnosis of a disease based on the theories of Chinese traditional medicine.
Most effective components are still unknown or have uncertain effects, as it is difficult to assign and test these components or their optimal combination.
At present, due to the lack of effective specific therapy, COVID-19 Chinese traditional medicine has become one of the main alternative treatments for patients with mild and moderate severity of symptoms, or for patients with post severe illness.
