The highest proportion of patients with COVID-19 has been reported in a number of provinces in China, where Chinese traditional medicine was used to treat 87 per cent of patients, including Ghana (63.7 per cent), Ninzi (50 per cent) and Hunan (50 per cent), while in Hubei Province, where Chinese traditional medicine was used to treat only approximately 30 per cent of patients with COVID-19, the lowest proportion of those cured (13 per cent) was recorded.
