Pneumonia is one of the most severe symptoms and is able to rapidly enter acute respiratory failure syndrome.
Despite the similarity of SARS-CoV and SARS-CoV-2, given the high homology of nucleoside sequences (82%), these viruses still form different branches of the phylogenetic tree.
SARS-CoV-2 is obviously less pathogenic but has a greater transfer capacity than SARS-CoV and MERS-CoV.
SARS-CoV-2 infection has been recorded, indicating that the virus is rapidly spreading throughout the world.
